definitions.definition: The goddess of the fertility of the Earth and harvests , protector of marriage and social order; daughter of Cronos and Rhea , mother to Persephone .

main_definition: ( Greek mythology ) The goddess of the fertility of the Earth and harvests , protector of marriage and social order; daughter of Cronos and Rhea , mother to Persephone .
secondary_definitions: ( astronomy ) 1108 Demeter , a main belt asteroid .
